definition: A globally unique identifier for an instance of a planned process (http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000082) that assigns a phenological trait annotation to a target plant observation based on human observation of a plant or part of the plant.
basis of record of oberserved organism.  See darwin core reference for values
name of the datasource
day of the year.  Must be between 1 and 366
latitude with precision up to 6 decimal places
longitude with precision up to 6 decimal places
scientific name of the observed organism
Trait tested.  Use trait values in traits.csv file corresponding to trait terms in the Plant Phenology Ontology.  E.g.  "flower present", "fruit present", "flower absent", or "fruit absent"
year of the observation
A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of media associated with the dwc:Occurrence.
coordinate uncertainty in meters
The full scientific name of the family in which the organism is classified.
The full scientific name of the genus in which the organism is classified.
individual ID of the observed organism
An identifier for the set of dcterms:Location information. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.
URL for the observation metadata hosted by the datasource.  For example https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/{observation_uuid}. This will resolve to a record.
occurrence ID of the observed organism

A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for recording the original dwc:Occurrence. The primary collector or observer, especially one who applies a personal identifier (dwc:recordNumber), should be listed first.
taxonomic rank of the scientific name
verbatim observation date
Verbatim description of the trait
A metric of accuracy for the annotations of only high certainty records based on expert, gold standard observations.
A metric of accuracy for the annotations of all records (equivocal and unequivocal) based on expert, gold standard observations.
Certainy of machine observation (Low or High).  This corresponds to Equivocal (Low) and Uniquevicol (High)
The number of records that were annotated at the taxon rank of family associated with the identified occurrence
Error messages from processing

A globally unique identifier for an instance of a planned process (http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000082) that assigns a phenological trait annotation to a target plant observation based on machine learning on an image that contains an image of the plant or part of the plant.
System inferred list of mapped traits with each trait separated by a pipe delimiter
URI landing page describing the model that was used.
Globally Unique Identifier of the image
URL for the image
a categorical description of the annotation outcome, in this case either "Detected" or "Not detected"
"A score from 0-1 which represent a scaled probability of presence or absence of a trait"

The proportion of the number of low certainty annotations divided by all annotations for iNaturalist observations in the taxonomic family. A metric of how successful the annotation process for observations in that family.
